@node Introduction "Workbench Boot Pictures Volume #3 - Introduction"

Introduction
------------

This is now the third and in my opinion the best collection of Workbench 
Boot Pictures that I have released for the Amiga.

Workbench Boot Pictures are simply a collection of IFF pictures for use with 
Joseph Luk's fabulous program, `BootScreen', to display a nice start-up
image while your Hard Disk is booting.  

`BootScreen' is a program which allows you to display an IFF picture while 
the hard drive is booting, much like the Microsoft Windows logo on the
IBM's.

I was influenced to draw these pictures after seeing the "rip-off" Microsoft 
Boot Pictures that were floating around and I thought the Amiga deserved
it's own exclusive Boot Screens.

So, I started work on some Boot Pictures that was exclusively "Amiga", and
related more to the Amiga OS, with this collection including pictures for
the latest Aniga Operating System, AmigaOS 3.1.

These pictures were drawn by hand exclusively with Deluxe Paint V with
colour touch ups and effects done with Art Department Professional 2.1.3
and Digital Illusions 1.0.

Although these pictures were designed in mind of OS 3.1 users, you may
change the OS and Release numbers to suit your own system (Please read
conditions in Copyright).

This volume contains many more pictures than any of the previous distributions 
which have many variations of one particular style.  Please refer to the
Discriptions section of this guide file for more details.  

@endnode



@node Description "Workbench Boot Pictures Volume #3 - Description"

Description
-----------

Bellow is a brief description of of the images included in this release of
Workbench Boot Pictures Volume #3:

WBBP-Funky31.iff	Black background, funky Helvetica typeface.
WBBP-GrFunky31.iff	Granite background, funky Helvetica typeface.
WBBP-GrPlain31.iff	Granite background, Helvetica typeface.
WBBP-GrPrest31.iff	Granite background, Prestige Helvetica typeface.
WBBP-MessTimes31.iff	Messy stone block, embossed Times typeface.
WBBP-Plain31.iff	Black background, Helvetica typeface.
WBBP-SlDiamond31.iff	Stone block, Helvetica typeface, OS3.1 logo diamond.
WBBP-SlPressed31.iff	Stone block, pressed Helvetica typeface.
WBBP-SlRaised31.iff	Stone block, logo and typography raised.
WBBP-SlTimes231.iff	Stone block, embossed Times typeface.
WBBP-SlTimes31.iff	Stone block, rased times typeface.

Total 11 pictures.

@endnode



@node Requirements "Workbench Boot Pictures Volume #3 - Requirements"

Requirements
------------

To use these pictures you will need:


* Either A500/A500/A1500/A2000/A2500/A3000 (16-Colour Pictures Only!) 
	 or
	 A1200/A4000 (All Pictures!)

* OS 2.0 or better 

* A Hard Disk

* `BootScreen' Version 2.2+ by Joseph Luk.


`BootScreen' is available on Aminet in the utils/boot directory.


@endnode



@node Installation "Workbench Boot Pictures Volume #3 - Installation"

Installation
------------

Firstly, if you have not done so already, you will need to install
`BootScreen', follow the instructions accompanied with the program
related the Install procedure.
 
After extracting the WB_BootPics3.lha file (well you must of got this far
if you are reading this guide!...), you will see a number of .IFF files, 
choose the pictures you want and copy them to your SYS:Prefs/Presets 
directory.  You can do this from the CLI by typing;



     copy <path containing WB_BootPics3 directory> SYS:Prefs/Presets


Or alternatively using a Disk Management Program Like Directory Opus.

After copying these files, load the BootScreen Prefs program in the Prefs 
directory of your SYS: partition and choose the desired Boot Screen
Picture.  You can choose the 'Test' Gadget to preview the picture you
want, then press 'Save' for BootScreen to save your options.

And thats all there is to it!

so next time you boot you machine, your desired BootPicture will be
displayed.

@endnode



